        <item>
          <actionDate>2015-05-19</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Andrew Prior Act or Andrew's Law</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Truth in Lending Act to discharge the repayment obligations of the estate of a borrower and any cosigner of a private educational loan if the borrower dies.</p> <p>The Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) must develop necessary and appropriate safeguards to prevent fraud and abuse in the discharge of those obligations. </p> <p>The CFPB may promulgate regulations to reinstate those obligations in any case in which it determines that doing so is necessary to protect the public interest.</p>]]></text>
